question6b.value:
Power analyses were made with G*Power:
o	As we will conduct an ANOVA with analyses of contrasts (comparison of 3 groups), “F tests” was selected as test family, with “ANOVA: Fixed effects, special, main effects and interactions” as statistical test, in an “A priori” type of power analysis.
o	The effect size f was set to a medium level of .25;
o	The conventional statistical significance level was set to α = .05 as usually done in our field;
o	The desired power was set to 1–β = .80 as recommended by Perugini, Gallucci and Costantini (2018);
o	The numerator df was set to 10;
o	As our IV will have 3 independent groups, the number of groups was set to 3.
The total sample size obtained was 269 participants. As this number is not divisible by 3, 270 participants was the total sample size selected.

